(4810, 'news', 250, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">&quot;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC has begun the procurement and supply process in all regions of the republic since January 01, 2017. Central warehouses have been identified in 12 regions and base stations in 55 regions and necessary staff has been involved for successful implementation of the process. Demands have been identified and contracts have been concluded with the procurement organizations. The management of the Company made a business trip to all regions of the republic and carried out monitoring of the procurement and supply process on the holiday days. The monitoring was carried out in all local structures where the Company was functioning- cities, regions, base stations included in Absheron, Guba - Khachmaz, Aran, Gakh - Zagatala, Sheki - Gabala, Shamkir - Gazakh, Ganja - Samukh, Upper Garabagh, Mountainous Shirvan and Lankaran Regional Offices. The management reviewed the central warehouses in the regions and instructed the staff of the local structures for the operational implementation of the procurement. It was stated at the meetings held in the regions that any interruption wouldn&rsquo;t occur in meeting the pre-determined requirements of the procurement organizations.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Regular monitoring of the procurement and supply process will be continued by the management of the Joint Stock Company.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/7575.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 563px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
(4811, 'news', 250, 'en', 'short', '\"Food Products’ Procurement and Supply” OJSC has begun the procurement and supply process in all regions of the republic since January 01, 2017. Central warehouses have been identified in 12 regions and base stations in 55 regions and necessary staff has been involved for successful implementation of the process. Demands have been identified and contracts have been concluded with the procurement organizations. The management of the Company made a business trip to all regions of the republic and carried out monitoring of the procurement and supply process on the holiday days. The monitoring was carried out in all local structures where the Company was functioning- cities, regions, base stations included in Absheron, Guba - Khachmaz, Aran, Gakh - Zagatala, Sheki - Gabala, Shamkir - Gazakh, Ganja - Samukh, Upper Garabagh, Mountainous Shirvan and Lankaran Regional Offices. The management reviewed the central warehouses in the regions and instructed the staff of the local structures for the operational implementation of the procurement. It was stated at the meetings held in the regions that any interruption wouldn’t occur in meeting the pre-determined requirements of the procurement organizations.'),
