(4884, 'news', 255, 'en', 'title', 'REGIONAL MEETINGS WILL BE HELD'),
(4885, 'news', 255, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC has started educating meetings with the procurement organizations to study supply level in the regions. A regional meeting was held in Sumgayit upon Absheron Regional Branch (Sumgait city, Absheron region, Khizi region) with the participation of the representatives of public procurement organizations. The representatives of Sumgayit city and Absheron region Executive Bodies, kindergartens and hospitals participated in the meeting.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors of &laquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC Khalig Mammadov made speech in the meeting and spoke about the development of the non-oil sector under the leadership of the head of the state in the recent years. He stated that, foundation of the Company by the President of Azerbaijan Republic would contribute to the formation of the supply chain in the agrarian sector, procurement of the products manufactured by farmers, as well as increase of the procurement level of the procurement organizations. The Company holds regional meetings, surveys and monitoring for increasing the procurement and supply level in line with the instructions of the head of the state. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The demand on the food stuff of the procurement organizations, rules of use of the electron portal (<a href=\"http://www.tedaruk.az\">www.tedaruk.az</a>), the instructions on the registration procedures were explained in the regional meeting. It was recommended to each procurement organization to post its demand correctly on the portal and the demands should be in line with real needs for proper use of the public funds. In this direction, many questions of the directors of kindergartens, representatives of hospitals were responded and their ability to work with the portal as explained in details. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Deputy Head of Sumgayit city Executive Body Lala Hajiyeva made speech in the meeting and highly estimated the establishment of the Company by the head of the country and emphasized that the level of supply of the procurement organizations by the food products has been increased in the city. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">At the end of the regional meeting, the representatives of the procurement organizations expressed their proposals for increasing the level of procurement and supply.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC will continue to hold the educating regional meetings with the procurement organizations in the regions. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/06-2.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 563px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
(4886, 'news', 255, 'en', 'short', '“Food Products’ Procurement and Supply” OJSC has started educating meetings with the procurement organizations to study supply level in the regions. A regional meeting was held in Sumgayit upon Absheron Regional Branch (Sumgait city, Absheron region, Khizi region) with the participation of the representatives of public procurement organizations. The representatives of Sumgayit city and Absheron region Executive Bodies, kindergartens and hospitals participated in the meeting.'),
