(4975, 'news', 261, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">A regional meeting was held in Masalli upon Lankaran Regional Division (Astara, Jalilabad, Masalli, Lankaran, Lerik and Yardimli) with the participation of the public procurement organizations and representatives of the executive bodies. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&nbsp;Making speech in the meeting, the Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors of &laquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&raquo; OJSC Khalig Mammadov spoke about the development of the non-oil sector under the leadership of the head of the state in the recent years. He stated that, foundation of the Company by the President of Azerbaijan Republic would contribute to the formation of the supply chain in the agrarian sector, procurement of the products manufactured by farmers, as well as increase of the procurement level of the procurement organizations. The Company holds regional meetings, surveys and monitoring for increasing the procurement and supply level in line with the instructions of the head of the state. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Stating the importance of the meetings held in the regions, Khalig Mammadov noted that these meetings aim to establish direct dialogue between the public procurement organizations and Joint Stock Companies, to explain the use of &ldquo;tedaruk.az&rdquo; electron portal, to learn the problems of the procurement organizations at place and to adopt decisions on their solution, to simplify communication with the agricultural manufactures. &quot;As stated by the head of the state, today Joint Stock Company is working on the mechanism of sustainable operation for purchasing the agricultural products just in the field from the manufactures and selling them to domestic and foreign markets,&quot; Khalig Mammadov said.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">He added that 120 kindergartens, 20 central hospitals, 86 executive offices and 6 other (totally 232) procurement organizations are supplied with qualitative food products upon Lankaran regional division.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The purpose of these meetings held in all regions is to reveal the production &ndash; procurement potential in the regions, to direct the products produced in the regions to the food demand of the public procurement organizations. If the food demand of the educational institutions, nurseries and kindergartens, hospitals and military units in each region is met on the account of the production capacities of the region, large volume of funds will enter the regions and local production will be stimulated. The main objective is supporting budget savings, ensuring transparency and supporting small and medium-sized businesses.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The demand on the food stuff of the procurement organizations, rules of use of the electron portal (<a href=\"http://www.tedaruk.az\">www.tedaruk.az</a>), the instructions on the registration procedures were explained in the regional meeting. It was recommended to each procurement organization to post its demand correctly on the portal and the demands should be in line with real needs for proper use of the public funds. In this direction, many questions of the directors of kindergartens, representatives of hospitals were responded and their ability to work with the portal as explained in details. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">At the end of the regional meeting, the representatives of the procurement organizations expressed their proposals for increasing the level of procurement and supply and procurement of local products.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/45.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 563px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
