(5004, 'news', 263, 'en', 'title', 'LOCAL PRODUCTS HAVE BEEN PROCURED FROM THE FRONTLINE'),
(5005, 'news', 263, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC has started collaborating with the manufacturers from the region since it began functioning. First of all, potential manufacturers from every region have been registered, their production power and annual production volume has been identified and contracts have been concluded for public utilization of to be produced products. These contracts are considered as state guarantees for each farmer.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Joint Stock Company purchases the products of the farmers at the average market price in order to protect their interests and realizes their sale at the fairs weekly organized in big cities. The procurement vehicles belonging to the company are in the regions in order to prevent the travel expenses and other expenses undergone by the farmers and the products are transported to the agricultural fairs on the account of the Company. The structural divisions located in 12 regions and the base stations located in 46 regions of the Company work actively in this area. A part of the procured products is directed to 1859 public procurement points &ndash; closed educational institutions, nursery - kindergartens, hospitals, military units and other state-owned facilities. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">As it is known, marketable onion has been produced more than demand in the harvest period in some regions this year. The Company procured the demand on onion of 1859 organizations procured by it &ndash; 1047 tons from the farmers in order to protect the manufacturers against loss and started the exportation of the remaining portion of onion to the markets of near foreign countries. As demand was high in the Russian markets, the company conducted negotiations with some concerned organizations and business men of Russia and reached an agreement on the exportation of onion of Azerbaijan. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Based on the protection of the economic interests of the people living in the frontline, the Company has managed to procure 1000 (a thousand) tons qualitative onion within the last two months and 600 (six hundred) tons within the last ten days, provided that they are purchased from Agdam, Agjabedi and Barda regions. Currently, the process is being continued and onions are purchased at the average market price and sent to the Russian markets every week.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&quot;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&quot; OJSC is preparing for the exportation of early products in connection with the beginning of spring - field season. The exportation of the early products to the foreign markets will be supported during the season.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/23.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
(5006, 'news', 263, 'en', 'short', '“Food Products’ Procurement and Supply” OJSC has started collaborating with the manufacturers from the region since it began functioning. First of all, potential manufacturers from every region have been registered, their production power and annual production volume has been identified and contracts have been concluded for public utilization of to be produced products. These contracts are considered as state guarantees for each farmer.'),
