(5035, 'news', 265, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">A business meeting was held with the representatives of &ldquo;Belgospisheprom&rdquo; State Concern of Belorussia Republic and the Belorussia Cooperatives Union at &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Firstly, Chairman of the Board of Directors Abulfat Gojayev gave detailed information about the activities of the company. He stated that, the purpose of Joint Stock Company is stimulating the production and processing of agricultural products, ensuring the development of the producers of the agricultural products, increasing the quality of food products, ensuring efficient use of public funds, improving the social welfare of the population engaged in the agriculture in the regions, ensuring fulfilment of procurement of the food products in the centralized order. 1000 (a thousand) ton agricultural products have been exported to the Russian markets through the Company and the exportation process is being continued. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">It was stated that the Company is interested in cooperation and exchange of experience with the analogical organizations of Belorussia Republic having strong agrarian potential. The Chairman of the Board of Directors proposed to export fruits and vegetables, fruit juices and other products depending on the season to Belorussia. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Deputy Chairman of the State Concern &quot;Belgospisheprom&quot; of Belorussia Republic Marina Mikhalsevich, head of foreign economic relations department of the concern Yelena Malinovskaya, head of foreign economic relations department of Belorussia Cooperatives Union (&quot;Belcoopsoyuz&quot;) Konstantin Rjeusskiy, head of the Consumer Products Export Department Sergey Alkhimovich spoke in the meeting and stated that they were interested in mutual collaboration. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Belarusian delegates proposed the importation of a range of agricultural products (carrot, cabbage, beet, potato, meat and dairy products) to Azerbaijan.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The parties agreed on the organization of mutual importation and exportation of agricultural products, exchange of experience, joint participation in the international events and on other issues in order to strengthen economic relations between Azerbaijan and Belorussia and it was decided to create a Working Group for deepening the cooperation in the near future in the discussions held between the parties. Next business meeting will be held in the near future to deepen cooperation.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">At the end, the guests from Belorussia were offered valuable gifts consisting of the national carpets of Azerbaijan. Later, the representatives made acquaintance with the storage conditions of the agricultural products stored in the warehouses of &laquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&raquo; OJSC.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">It was noted that it was decided to establish cooperation in the procurement and supply field between two countries in the meeting of the Intergovernmental Economic Commission held in Minsk in November of the last year with the participation of the president of Azerbaijan Republic Ilham Aliyev and the president of Belorussia Republic Alexander Lukashenko and in the meeting of the Economic Trade Commission held in December of the same year with the participation of the Minister of Economy Shahin Mustafayev.</span></span></p>'),
