(5080, 'news', 268, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">A commemoration ceremony was held at &quot;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&quot; OJSC on March 31 on the occasion of the Day of Genocide of Azerbaijanis. The memory of the victims of the genocide was commemorated with a minute of silence at the ceremony held with the participation of the staff of the company. The video film proving the genocide with facts was watched. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors Elshan Asadov spoke in the ceremony and stated that our National Leader Heydar Aliyev had signed a Decree on March 26, 1998 for commemorating all genocides committed against our people and not forgetting these tragedies and declared March 31 as the Day of Genocide of Azerbaijanis. The true essence of the bloody genocide and deportation committed against our people for centuries, but purposefully concealed has begun to be investigated by the historians, archivists and dark pages have been elucidated after that historical decree. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The historian scientist Nizami Mammadov gave a talk on March massacres held in Baku in 1918 and the policy of ethnic cleansing and genocide of Armenians against Azerbaijani people at the beginning of the XX century, merciless crimes committed by the dashnaks in Baku, massacres committed in Shamakhi and Guba in the spring of 1918, in Garabagh, Goychay, Zangazur and Nakhchivan in 1918.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">March 31 &ndash; Day of Genocide of Azerbaijani people was written as a bloody event of the XX century in our history. Our thousands of innocent, peaceful compatriots were brutally murdered by organized Armenian groups during the genocide. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Speaking about the necessity of remembering the event and bringing it to the world community, the specialist on Public Relations of the Company Nijat Nasirli emphasized that enough work is done by our state in this direction, but there are circles who have difficulties in accepting the truths of Azerbaijan due to double standards in the world. Other speakers also spoke about the Armenian terrorism and its history, the Dashnaksutun party having great services in the implementation of March genocide, the work done to realize the idea of ​​creating &quot;Great Armenia&quot; and the policy of ethnic cleansing against Azerbaijanis.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The event was continued with discussions.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/0177.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
(5081, 'news', 268, 'en', 'short', 'A commemoration ceremony was held at \"Food Products’ Procurement and Supply\" OJSC on March 31 on the occasion of the Day of Genocide of Azerbaijanis. The memory of the victims of the genocide was commemorated with a minute of silence at the ceremony held with the participation of the staff of the company. The video film proving the genocide with facts was watched. '),
