(5095, 'news', 269, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"background:yellow;\"><span style=\"background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&quot;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&quot; OJSC has approved the internal rules for realizing advance payments to the manufactures of agricultural products. These Rules have been designed for ensuring the execution of sub-article 3.6.3 &ldquo;Regulations on purchase of foodstuffs by state enterprises and organizations at the account of the state budget in the centralized order&rdquo; approved by Decree No. 859 dated April 11, 2016 of the President of Azerbaijan Republic Ilham Aliyev and defines the order of realization of advance payment to producers or sellers of food products.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"background:yellow;\"><span style=\"background-color:#FFFFFF;\">According to Article 1.2 of Regulations, 25 percent of the amount of goods to be purchased by &laquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&raquo; OJSC (excluding processed food products) at the duly fixed price in next year will be paid as advance payment till October 31 to the food manufacturers or sellers. Advance payment is paid by transfer to the settlement account of the manufacturers or sellers being legal entities or to the current account of the physical entities. Realization of advance payments to the manufacturers or sellers is carried out by the Commission consisting of a chairman, a Deputy Chairman and 5 members established under the Company. The Commission deals with the list of products to be ordered for supply or procurement for next year, informing the agricultural manufacturers on terms and conditions of application and required documents through the regional structure units or declaring them in the official web site of the Company. According to the distribution provided for in Article 4.3 of this Regulation, advance payment to the manufacturers and sellers in the amount from 3 thousand to 50 thousand will be realized according to the decision of the Commission and in the amount more than 50 thousand according to the decision of the Board of Directors.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF ADVANCE PAYMENTS</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The manufacturer or seller submits an application made in accordance with Appendix 1 to this Regulation to the Commission either electronically or in writing from April 01 to September 01&nbsp; to receive an advance payment for product or products to be produced or sold on the basis of the order of the Company in the following year. The following documents are also attached to that application:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&bull;&nbsp; Data on the manufacturer (legal documents, plot of land, technical facilities, equipment and personnel)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&bull;&nbsp; If the plot of land is leased, then the lease agreement signed by the representative of the PRD of the executive power for 5 hectare or by the notary public for more than 5 hectare. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&bull;&nbsp; Reference on tax payable</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&bull;&nbsp; Extract from the Central Credit Registry (whether it is a loan debtor)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&bull;&nbsp; Detailed information on qualitative indicators on the relevant criteria (sort, measurement, composition, purity, physical condition, packaging and etc.) of to be grown and to be offered products.&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Society may, at any time, examine the site of the manufacturer whom it cooperates with, get familiar with the field service process, take samples from the products and inform the manufacturer about the identified deficiencies and require elimination of deficiencies.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">AMOUNT OF ADVANCE PAYMENT AND ITS CALCULATION ORDER </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The total amount of advances given for each agricultural product is regulated separately upon small, medium and large-scale producer categories. The amount of advance payments can be up to 3,000 manat for small producers, 50,000 manat for medium-sized producers and up to 250,000 manat for large-scale manufacturers. An advance payment may be made to a producer for several products separately for each product category. However, the total advance amount can&rsquo;t be greater than the maximum amount considered for large - scale manufacturers. All information provided by the manufacturer to the Company must be accurate.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">PRODUCT PURCHASE ORDER </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The purchase price of each sort of the foodstuffs is fixed by the Ministry of Agriculture of Azerbaijan Republic in agreement with the Ministry of Economy of Azerbaijan Republic. Manufacturer undertakes to sell the agricultural product to the Company manufactured in the amount equal to the amount of advance payment if he isn&rsquo;t satisfied with the fixed purchase price. If the manufacturer rejects to sell the product in the amount equal to the advance payment, the advance payment shall be paid back within 10 (ten) days calculating the accrued interests in accordance with the discount rate defined by the Central Bank of Azerbaijan Republic for that period. If the qualitative indicators of grown or delivered products are not as expected, the company may reduce its price (apply the average market price of the similar products) or generally refuse to purchase. In this case, the advance payment shall be paid back within 10 (ten) days calculating the accrued interests in accordance with the discount rate defined by the Central Bank of Azerbaijan Republic for that period.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The data on the manufacturers whom advances were issued shall be posted on the official internet site of the Company in accordance with the decision of the commission and results obtained on each manufacturer are regularly added to that information. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Company&#39;s Internal Control Service carries out regular control measures independently (without participation of other departments) regarding the issuance of advances to the producers and the efficient use of the budgetary funds and the results are reported to the Board of Directors of the Company every month. The services of the independent audit companies are used by the Company whenever it is necessary to ensure the transparency in the process of issuance of advances. This Regulation can be modified by the decision of the Board of Directors of the Company. However, the full awareness of the producers is ensured.</span></span></p>'),
