(5154, 'news', 273, 'en', 'title', '\"ADVANCE PAYMENT DAY\" IN TOVUZ'),
(5155, 'news', 273, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&quot;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&quot; OJSC has approved the internal rules for payment of advances to the producers of agricultural products. These rules have been approved by Decree No. 859 dated April 11, 2016 of the President of Azerbaijan Republic, have been drawn up for ensuring the execution of sub-article 3.6.3 &ldquo;Regulations on purchase of foodstuffs by state enterprises and organizations at the account of the state budget in the centralized order&rdquo; and specifies the procedure of advance payment to food manufacturers. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The total amount of advances given for each agricultural product is regulated separately upon small, medium and large-scale producer categories. The amount of advance payments can be up to 3,000 manat for small producers, 50,000 manat for medium-sized producers and up to 250,000 manat for large-scale manufacturers. An advance payment may be made for a single product, for each product, separately for each product category. However, the total advance amount can not be greater than the maximum recommended by major manufacturers. An advance payment may be made to a producer for several products separately for each product category. However, the total advance amount can&rsquo;t be greater than the maximum amount considered for large - scale producers.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC carried out the next stage of advance payment to the manufacturers this week. The presentation of advance payment was carried out in Hunanlar village of Tovuz region on May 02, 2017. The representative of the Executive Power of Tovuz region Adalat Ismayilov and the Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Company Elshan Asadov spoke at the event and gave information about economical importance of the advance system. Then, advance in the amount 90 thousand and 861 manat was paid to 18 farmers from Tovuz, Gazakh, Shamkir and Gadabay regions. The funds were given for increasing the production of potato, carrot and beet in the mentioned regions.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/IMG_1124.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/IMG_1138.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/IMG_1206.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
(5156, 'news', 273, 'en', 'short', '\"Food Products’ Procurement and Supply\" OJSC has approved the internal rules for payment of advances to the producers of agricultural products. These rules have been approved by Decree No. 859 dated April 11, 2016 of the President of Azerbaijan Republic, have been drawn up for ensuring the execution of sub-article 3.6.3 “Regulations on purchase of foodstuffs by state enterprises and organizations at the account of the state budget in the centralized order” and specifies the procedure of advance payment to food manufacturers. '),
