(5170, 'news', 274, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&quot;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&quot; OJSC has approved the internal rules for payment of advances to the producers of agricultural products. These rules have been approved by Decree No. 859 dated April 11, 2016 of the President of Azerbaijan Republic, have been drawn up for ensuring the execution of sub-article 3.6.3 &ldquo;Regulations on purchase of foodstuffs by state enterprises and organizations at the account of the state budget in the centralized order&rdquo; and specifies the procedure of advance payment to food manufacturers. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The total amount of advances given for each agricultural product is regulated separately upon small, medium and large-scale producer categories. The amount of advance payments can be up to 3,000 manat for small producers, 50,000 manat for medium-sized producers and up to 250,000 manat for large-scale manufacturers. An advance payment may be made for a single product, for each product, separately for each product category. However, the total advance amount can not be greater than the maximum recommended by major manufacturers. An advance payment may be made to a producer for several products separately for each product category. However, the total advance amount can&rsquo;t be greater than the maximum amount considered for large - scale producers.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The next presentation of advance payment was carried out on the areas along Kura River of Yevlakh region, the Deputy Chairman of the Executive Power of the region Ganimat Garashov and the Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Company Elshan Asadov spoke about proper use of funds by the farmers and the economic importance of the process conducted on the basis of the instructions given by the head of the state. Several farmers spoke at the event and estimated the allocation of funds as the next support of the state to the agrarian area.&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The advance in the amount 197 thousand and 500 manat was paid to 20 farmers. The farmers from Aghjabadi, Aghdash, Barda, Jalilabad, Yevlakh, Gakh, Zardab, Neftchala, Saatli, Imishli and Zagatala regions will achieve the production of goods replacing the import.&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/IMG_1453.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/IMG_1483.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
(5171, 'news', 274, 'en', 'short', '\"Food Products’ Procurement and Supply\" OJSC has approved the internal rules for payment of advances to the producers of agricultural products. These rules have been approved by Decree No. 859 dated April 11, 2016 of the President of Azerbaijan Republic, have been drawn up for ensuring the execution of sub-article 3.6.3 “Regulations on purchase of foodstuffs by state enterprises and organizations at the account of the state budget in the centralized order” and specifies the procedure of advance payment to food manufacturers. '),
