(5199, 'news', 276, 'en', 'title', '“FAMOUS JAPANESE COMPANIES CAN COOPERATE WITH THE JOINT STOCK COMPANY”'),
(5200, 'news', 276, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\">A business meeting was conducted between the Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors Elshan Asadov of &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC and the Attach&eacute; on economic issues of the Embassy of Japan to Azerbaijan Toshihiro Katagari in the central office of the Company. The purpose of the meeting was the discussion of the perspectives of increase of the commercial turnover between two countries. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\">E. Asadov gave wide information about the economic reforms carried out in Azerbaijan. He stated that the establishment of the Joint Stock Company by the head of the state was the support of the agrarian reforms in the country. Within five months of its establishment, the organization has completed the procurement and supply system and has started to give advance payments to the producers. The organization is interested in studying Japanese experience in this area, as well as applying scientific and technical innovations in farming and intends to cooperate with relevant Japanese institutions in this area.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\">Attach&eacute; Toshihiro Katagiri spoke about the existence of similar government institutions in the field of procurement and supply system in his country and said that they were interested in the cooperation with &laquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&raquo; OJSC. The diplomat said that, cooperation in the field of exchange of experience could lead to further expansion of economic relations in the future: &ldquo;While Japanese companies are active in the energy sector of Azerbaijan, they are less in the non-oil sector. We shall try to make these companies be interested in agriculture. I would like to note that there is great interest in a number of products of Azerbaijan - pomegranate, date, feykhoa, cherry, fig, apricot and other products in Japan. If the requirements such as marking and packaging are fulfilled, the products of Azerbaijan can easily find way to remote Japan markets. A number of well-known Japanese companies can cooperate with &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC in this field. There are successful cooperation perspectives in the field of application of modern technologies in farms, establishment of farmers&#39; accounting system, and marketing of products. &quot;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\">It was decided to hold a business meeting with Japanese companies in the near future and to organize a visit of the representatives of &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC for exchange of experiences.</span></span></p>'),
(5201, 'news', 276, 'en', 'short', 'A business meeting was conducted between the Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors Elshan Asadov of “Food Products’ Procurement and Supply” OJSC and the Attaché on economic issues of the Embassy of Japan to Azerbaijan Toshihiro Katagari in the central office of the Company. The purpose of the meeting was the discussion of the perspectives of increase of the commercial turnover between two countries. '),
