(5229, 'news', 278, 'en', 'title', 'JOINT STOCK COMPANY PARTICIPATED IN THE INTERNATIONAL EXHIBITION'),
(5230, 'news', 278, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Today, &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC&nbsp;&nbsp; is represented by 100 m<sup>2</sup> stand at the XXIII Azerbaijan International Food Industry Exhibition &ldquo;WorldFood Azerbaijan 2017&rdquo; organized in Baku Expo Center. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Attending the opening ceremony of the exhibition, the President of Azerbaijan Republic Ilham Aliyev has got closely acquainted with the products presented by OJSC and given his instructions and recommendations. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Joint Stock Company participates at the exhibition with medium-sized tractors jointly with the Chinese State Corporation &ldquo;YTO GROUP&rdquo;.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Let&rsquo;s note that, according to the agreement between &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC and &ldquo;YTO GROUP&rdquo;, averagely 800 medium-sized (18-40 horsepower) YTO tractors will be assembled per a year at the production facility in Gusar region. It was decided to allocate loans for exportation of the spare parts of tractors as the result of negotiations held with the Chinese company. Other spare parts except tractor engines and transmission facilities will be purchased from various enterprises operating in Azerbaijan from the second year and it will exert positive impact on the development of additional various industries. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">YTO tractors that will be jointly manufactured will be sold to our local farmers under favourable conditions through &ldquo;Agrolizing&rdquo; OJSC. After payment of 20% of the value, the rest amount will be divided into equal instalments for 10 years (120 months), thus, farmers will be able to buy a tractor by paying small amount. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Simplicity of the technical specifications of YTO tractors, ease of use will allow farmers to use the technique without any additional vocational training. Compared with alternative brands, these tractors are distinguished by low cost, availability of high pressure fuel pump, power, spare parts quality and reasonable price, low fuel consumption. YTO tractors are widely used in gardening, vegetable growing, tobacco cultivation, feed growing and greenhouse industries. According to the researches, there is great need for small-sized tractors in the farms of our country. In particular, these techniques will play an important role in reducing labour costs in small households, ensuring the production process intensity and reducing losses. Tractor carries out inter-row technical works, cultivation measures, field harvesting and other important work in a short term allowing to work in small sowing areas. Establishment of production of YTO tractors in Azerbaijan will contribute to rapid renovation of the agricultural machinery and technique park.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">For reference, &ldquo;YTO GROUP&rdquo; of China is the state owned corporation and its annual production capacity is 120,000 tractors and 230,000 engines. The Corporation manufactures all series of chain and wheel tractors ranging from 18 horsepower to 380 horsepower, engines, combines and agricultural tools. Cooperating with more than 100 countries of the world, the Company has established its service networks in these countries and achieved exportation of 20,000 tractors within three years. The exportation volume was 100 million USD in 2015.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/333.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 499px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
