(5274, 'news', 281, 'en', 'title', 'NEW AREAS ARE DEVELOPED THANKS TO ADVANCE PAYMENTS'),
(5275, 'news', 281, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC carries out expansion of cultivation of the grain &ndash; leguminous plants on great demand removed from the sowing structure of the country for many years for some reasons as the next stage of development of households. A great part of the advance payments issued in all regions of the republic is directed to expansion of cultivation of the grain &ndash; leguminous plants. One of these plants is buckwheat. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">As is known, buckwheat is one of the plants taking an important place in the consumption of the people and having high nutritional value. The lack of demand for agro-technical service, easy cultivation in non- fertile soils, resistance against severe climate factors enhances the economic importance of this plant.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">As it hasn&rsquo;t been cultivated for long term in the regions of our republic, at present, it is imported from the neighbourhood states. Joint Stock Company carries out payment of advances in this field and purchase of produced product from the farmer at favourable price in order to increase the interest of the manufactures in the buckwheat cultivation. Cultivation of buckwheat has been started for the first time in this season. 39 thousand 348 manat advance payment was issued to the producers for cultivation of buckwheat on 50 hectare plot of land in Kurdemir (expected productivity 125 ton), on 12 hectare plot of land in Gabala (expected productivity 30 ton) and on 1 hectare plot of land in Barda (expected productivity 125 ton). Sowing was completed in the optimal time and at present, plantation corresponding to the agro-technical rules has been achieved in the fields. The forecasted productivity from the fields will be 157.5 tons. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Today, the Head of the Monitoring and Commodity Turnover Coordination Department of the Joint Stock Company Sahib Shukurov and employees of the regional division visited the field of the resident of Tuntul village, Gabala region Elchin Bakhishov and examined the development phase of the plant. The farmer received 10,680 manat advance payment for cultivation of buchwheat on 12 hectare area. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Joint Stock Company has given 2 million 712 thousand manat to 120 farmers for cultivation of 39 sorts of plants including pea, bean, cabbage, carrot, potato, lettuce, rice paddy and other plants during this year&rsquo;s season. The volume of procurement upon the issued advance payments will be 25 thousand 526 ton. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">During this year&#39;s harvest season, 120 farmers were given 2 million 712 thousand manat on 39 types of products, including buckwheat, chickpeas, beans, garlic, cabbage, carrots, potatoes, lettuce, pheasant and other products. The volume of deliveries on the given advances will be 25 thousand 526 tons.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/IMG-20170530-WA0046.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 563px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
