(5304, 'news', 283, 'en', 'title', 'THE DELEGATION OF JOINT STOCK COMPANY VISITED BAHRAIN KINGDOM'),
(5305, 'news', 283, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The delegation of &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC was on business trip in Bahrain Kingdom. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The delegation included the chairman of the Board of Directors Abulfat Gojayev, Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors Elshan Asadov and the representatives of the company functioning in the nutrition sector. The purpose of the visit was the exportation of the products of Azerbaijan to the Gulf Countries, investigation of alternative markets and involving foreign investments to the agrarian sector of our country. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The first business meeting was with the president of &ldquo;Mumtalakat Holding&rdquo; Mahmud Alkhochayi. It was decided to establish partnership between the Holding and Joint Stock Company, to invest in some fields of the agricultural production, to develop Transport Logistics Project for transportation of goods of Azerbaijan to Gulf countries in the rational meeting. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The next business meeting was conducted with the Chief Executive director of &quot;Arcapita&quot; Investment Fund Atif Abdulmalik. The executive director stated that the Fund had invested about 30 billion dollars in 70 enterprises and cooperation with the companies of Azerbaijan can be established in this direction. The representatives of the Joint Stock Company made an extensive presentation on the economic potential of Azerbaijan. Mr. Atif Abdulmalik expressed his interest in participating in the project of Logistics Center to be built in Azerbaijan and held detailed discussions in this subject. Mr. Galpin said that the council has large scaled investments in the field of financial services, production, tourism, logistics and transport. The Council is interested in providing these sectors with the state support in connection with the export of foodstuffs from Azerbaijan Republic, as well as the expansion of logistics opportunities.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Mutual presents were made at the end of the meeting. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The delegation of the Joint Stock Company also met with the member of Bahrain Royal Family, the president of &ldquo;Riyada Group of Companies&rdquo; Mrs. Sheikha Deya Bin Ibrahim Al Khalifa. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Chairman of the Board of Directors of &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC Abulfat Gojayev gave detailed information about the agricultural potential and economic reforms held in Azerbaijan. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Mrs. Sheikha stated she was aware about the quality of products of Azerbaijan and she was ready to support the establishment of the network of sale of the products of Azerbaijan in Bahrain. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">At the end of the meeting, Mrs. Sheika was presented a carpet and silk kerchief of Azerbaijan.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The presentation exhibition of the products of Azerbaijan was organized by &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC for the companies of Bahrain on the last day of the business meetings. The products of &ldquo;Meyveli&rdquo;, &ldquo;Balkhurma&rdquo;, &ldquo;Gilan&rdquo;, &ldquo;Azersun&rdquo;, &ldquo;Balli&rdquo;, &ldquo;Veyseloghlu&rdquo;, &ldquo;Milla&rdquo;, &ldquo;AzGranata&rdquo;, &ldquo;GlobalFoodService&rdquo;, &ldquo;AhmedTodor&rdquo;, &ldquo;AstaraChay&rdquo;, &ldquo;Goch Et&rdquo; and &ldquo;Tovuz Baltiya&rdquo; companies were exhibited at the exhibition held in the central building of &ldquo;Riyada Group&rdquo; and tasting was conducted. Our products were highly appreciated both for their appearance and taste by the businessmen of Bahrain. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Numerous proposals were made about the exportation of products of Azerbaijan to Bahrain Kingdom and views were exchanged at the exhibition. The Vice-President of &ldquo;Riyada Group&rdquo; Sergey Tsektov suggested to open the sales market of products of Azerbaijani in Bahrain and stated that they were ready for cooperation in this direction. It was decided to sign a memorandum of cooperation.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The delegation of &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC and Azerbaijani entrepreneurs visited the market networks of the capital of Bahrain Kingdom &ndash; Manama within the framework of the visit and examined the internal market prices of the foodstuffs. It was known as a result of the examinations carried out at &ldquo;Carrefur&rdquo; and other sales network that the price of vegetable, fruits and other foodstuffs was more expensive in comparison with Azerbaijan and besides, their quality wasn&rsquo;t satisfactory. To this end, exportation of agricultural products from Azerbaijan Republic is possible. If the logistic opportunities are formed, products of Azerbaijan can be sold at high price and compete for their quality indicators in a short term in the markets of Bahrain.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/2158.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 422px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/2065.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 563px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/2115.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 563px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/2119.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 563px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
