(5334, 'news', 285, 'en', 'title', 'JOINT STOCK COMPANY WILL COOPERATE WITH “RIYADA GROUP”'),
(5335, 'news', 285, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">A memorandum of understanding was signed between &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC and &ldquo;Riyada Consulting&rdquo; included in &ldquo;Riyada Group&rdquo; holding of Bahrain Kingdom on the establishment of strategic partnership. The document was signed on one hand by the Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Joint Stock Company Abulfat Gojayev and on the other hand by Sergey Tsvetkov. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The parties will cooperate in the exportation of the products of Azerbaijan to the Gulf Countries, investigation of alternative markets and involving foreign investments to the agrarian sector of our country. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">As there is great demand in the products of Azerbaijan in the markets of the Gulf Countries, &ldquo;Riyada Consulting&rdquo; will render consulting services in finding new customers on the basis of the mutual agreement. The Joint Stock Company will be responsible for procurement of the products corresponding to the demand of foreign markets and the other party will be responsible for management of sales on the determined territories.&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">A working group was established for realization of the cooperation. The Group will be managed by the Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors Elshan Asadov on behalf of the Joint Stock Company and by Sergey Tsvetkov on behalf of the company from Bahrain. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">&ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC carries out successive works in the direction of exportation of products of Azerbaijan to Gulf Countries. Some time ago, the delegation of the Joint Stock Company visited Bahrain Kingdom and United Arab Emirates and conducted discussions with the managements of many holdings and sales networks. The delegation of the company conducted business meetings with the president of &ldquo;Mumtalakat&rdquo; Holding Mahmud Alkhochayi, the chief executive director of &ldquo;Bahrain Economic development Board&rdquo; Simon Galpin, member of Bahrain Royal Family, the president of &ldquo;Riyada Group of Companies&rdquo; Mrs. Sheikha Deya Bin Ibrahim Al Khalifa and made presentation on the economic reforms carried out in Azerbaijan and the agricultural potential of our country. As the continuation of the discussions, the presentation exhibition of the products of Azerbaijan was organized by &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC for the companies of Bahrain on the last day of the business meetings. The products of &ldquo;Meyveli&rdquo;, &ldquo;Balkhurma&rdquo;, &ldquo;Gilan&rdquo;, &ldquo;Azersun&rdquo;, &ldquo;Balli&rdquo;, &ldquo;Veyseloghlu&rdquo;, &ldquo;Milla&rdquo;, &ldquo;AzGranata&rdquo;, &ldquo;GlobalFoodService&rdquo;, &ldquo;AhmedTodor&rdquo;, &ldquo;AstaraChay&rdquo;, &ldquo;Goch Et&rdquo; and &ldquo;Tovuz Baltiya&rdquo; companies were exhibited at the exhibition held in the central building of &ldquo;Riyada Group&rdquo; and tasting was conducted. Our products were highly appreciated both for their appearance and taste by the businessmen of Bahrain. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The delegation of &ldquo;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&rdquo; OJSC and Azerbaijani entrepreneurs visited the market networks of the capital of Bahrain Kingdom &ndash; Manama within the framework of the visit and examined the internal market prices of the foodstuffs. It was known as a result of the examinations carried out at &ldquo;Carrefur&rdquo; and other sales network that the price of vegetable, fruits and other foodstuffs was more expensive in comparison with Azerbaijan and besides, their quality wasn&rsquo;t satisfactory. To this end, exportation of agricultural products from Azerbaijan Republic is possible. If the logistic opportunities are formed, products of Azerbaijan can be sold at high price and compete for their quality indicators in a short term in the markets of Bahrain.</span></span></p>'),
