(5440, 'news', 292, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Opening the meeting, the Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Joint Stock Company Khalig Mammadov spoke about the organization and the procurement and supply system established upon the country. Kh.Mammadov stated that necessary infrastructure has been established for normal functioning of the organization founded by Order N 1944 dated April 2016 of the President of Azerbaijan Republic Ilham Aliyev, 12 regional divisions and base stations in 46 regions have been established and their main logistics center is located in Baku and administrative buildings, as well as warehouses have been leased for the regional divisions and necessary equipment has been supplied. At present, the Joint Stock Company possesses storage facilities with more than 19&nbsp;000 m2 total capacity. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The deputy chairman stated that contracts have been concluded with 863 procurement organizations for supplying 1919 supply points with products. An electron portal (www.tedaruk.az) was established in accordance with &ldquo;the Regulations on purchase of food products at the state account in the centralized order by the public enterprises and organizations&rdquo; approved by the relevant Decree of the President of Azerbaijan Republic and commissioned on November 08, 2016. Since that date, purchase announcements on 173 sorts of products have been posted on that portal on the basis of demand of the procurement organizations. Public procurement organizations financed by the state budget have been provided with 37 thousand ton products upon 18 sorts within 9 months of 2017 and the amount of the purchased products was 66 million 497 thousand manat. Its great part was purchased from local producers (including 395 farmers and 276 companies) and it means that large amount of funds entered into the turnover of the local producers. The demand volume of the procurement organizations for 2018 was identifies as 79 thousand and 409 ton. It means that, more funds will be paid to local producers. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">With respect to advance payment for production, announcements have been made by the Joint Stock Company in mass media since April of this year and extensive propaganda work has been carried out. As a result of this process, applications on various products were received from 309 producers. Those producers will be monitored, 2,729,459 manat advance payment was provided on 11 sorts of products to 123 farms whose production potential and accuracy of the submitted documents had been certified. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Joint Stock Company Elshan Asadov made speech in the meeting and stated that necessary steps have been taken for establishment of international relations, exportation of local products to foreign markers, establishment of relations with the sales network of big countries by the company with 9 months. The company has organized its operations actively in exportation of the remaining portion of products to the world markets and supporting local production. 81.3 thousand ton agricultural product were directly procured from the producers and directed to supply of procurement organisations or to the internal and external markets in January &ndash; September of this year. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The speaker emphasized that one of the successes achieved during the past period was the place taken by the Joint Stock Company in the rating of state owned countries participating in the exportation operations in non-oil sector. Thus, according to exportation round up on non-oil sector for 9 months of 2017, &quot;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&quot;&nbsp;OJSC took the 5<sup>th</sup> place with 32.2 million dollar exportation volume. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Then, a number of perspective issues of mutual interest were discussed. Views were exchanged on such subjects as establishment of the regional procurement base in the near future in accordance with the complex measures defined in the &ldquo;Strategic Road Map upon national economical perspective of Azerbaijan Republic&rdquo;, supporting small farms, establishment of mutual economic relations with the producers, increasing the sorts of the procured products, improvement of advance mechanism, strengthening of the activities of the regional offices, supplying procurement organizations with more qualitative product. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Speakers in the meeting expressed their confidence that the tasks set before the Joint Stock Company by the President of the country will be properly implemented.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The head of the structural offices have been given instructions necessary for further improvement of the procurement and supply system.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/22792501_2014634735487228_2522714992849814240_o.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/22791720_2014634838820551_463613247222483513_o.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
