(5589, 'news', 302, 'en', 'title', 'JOINT STOCK COMPANY COMPLETED THE YEAR WITH SUCCESSFULL RESULTS'),
(5590, 'news', 302, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">A report meeting devoted to the outcomes of 2017 and upcoming tasks was held at the Open Joint Stock Company &quot; Food products&rsquo; procurement and supply&quot;.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Opening the meeting, Chairman of the Board Mr. Abulfat Gojayev gave detailed information on the work done by the Joint Stock Company last year. During the reporting period, 863 procurement agencies financed from the state budget signed contracts with 1865 supply points.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Procurement agencies financed by the state budget in 2017 are supplied with food products worth 97 million manat in 18 product categories. Most of it (395 farmers and 276 companies) have been purchased from local producers, which means that large amounts of funds are included in the turnover of domestic producers.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Chairman of the Board Abulfat Gojayev also touched upon the export issues, which were made at the report. He said that in order to export agricultural products to foreign markets, regular studies were conducted in foreign markets, proposals of entrepreneurs were discussed and for the export of domestic products, cooperation letters were sent to the food companies located in countries such as Russia, Belarus, Ukraine, the Czech Republic, France, UAE, Bahrain, Qatar Emirate and several productive meetings were held with them. An agreement on cooperation with Russia&#39;s two major trading companies has been signed. As a result of the export-related activities, export of goods worth more than 54 million 928 thousand manat was carried out.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">With respect to advance payment for production, since April of the current year, the Company has made public announcements in mass media and wide propagandistic work. As a result of this process the application from 309 manufacturers has been received for different products. By monitoring those manufacturers, during the spring and autumn season 3 544 488 manat advance payment was made to the 132 business entities which production potential and accuracy of submitted documents were confirmed, for production of 11 products.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Based on the results of the Monitoring on the Performance Status of the &quot;Strategic Road Map on Agricultural Products Production and Processing in the Republic of Azerbaijan&quot;, the activities carried out by the Joint-Stock Company were assessed at 50 points by calculating with 100-point system on the Performance of the Main Executing Agencies Scale.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Speaking at the reporting meeting of the Board of Directors Deputy Chairpersons -Khalig Mammadov, Elshan Asadov and department heads spoke about the results achieved in the year ended. The speakers voiced their opinions on the priorities to be implemented in 2018.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/334.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/335.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
