(5815, 'news', 314, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/Sedr/6.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The &quot;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&quot; OJSC has started the organization of sale fairs in order to increase the supply of the capital&#39;s population with agricultural products and to prevent artificial price increases regarding to the upcoming Novruz holiday. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Fairs:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Sabail district, Badamdar settlement, Seyran Mammadov Street 1;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Nasimi district, Mardanov Gardashlari Street 59;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Yasamal district, Abbas Mirza Sharifzadeh street 207;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Surakhani district, Amirjan settlement, Sattar Bahlulzadeh street;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Surakhani district, Yeni Gunashli settlement. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The products offered to the population at the fair were supplied by local producers from the regional point of the Joint-Stock Company and at the same time, farmers who want to sell their products in the capital received organizational support. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">At the fairs to be held on Saturdays and Sundays, more than 30 tons and 70 types of agricultural and food products will be provided on daily basis. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Joint Stock Company has also distributed peanuts, white beans, buckwheat and rice products, which are packaged under the brand &quot;Eloba&quot; and supplied from local farmers at the expense of advance. All products will be sold on average of 20 percent cheaper than market prices. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The fairs will run until the end of March.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/Sedr/4.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
