(5905, 'news', 320, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"background:white;\">&ldquo;<em><span style=\"font-style:normal;\">Food Products</span></em>&#39;&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-style:normal;\">Procurement and Supply</span></em>&rdquo; <em><span style=\"font-style:normal;\">OJSC</span></em> held a commemorative event dedicated to the 100-th anniversary of the March 31, Genocide of Azerbaijanis</span>. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Firstly, the victims of the genocide were commemorated with a minute of silence. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Elshan Asadov, Deputy Chairman of the Board of Directors, spoke about the genocide committed against our people and conveyed the state-level work done to bring historical truths to the world community. He emphasized that March 31 was proclaimed as the Day of Genocide of Azerbaijanis by the Decree of the National Leader Heydar Aliyev dated March 26, 1998. By the initiative of President Ilham Aliyev, steps have been taken to bring the bloody events against our people to the international level. &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Nuri Mammadov, doctor of Historical Sciences and lecturer of the Baku State University, disclosed the details of the genocide committed against our people and analyzed the intense geopolitical situation that occurred in the early 20th century. Historian scientist said that the Armenian armed forces from the Baku-Dashnaktsutiun committed massacre against the Azerbaijanis in Baku, as well as in Shamakhi, Guba, Khachmaz, Lankaran, Hajigabul, Salyan, Zangezur, Garabagh, Nakhchivan and other areas From March 30 to April 3, 1918.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Speaking about the national resistance movement against the Armenian aggression in the territory of Azerbaijan, the speaker conveyed historical steps taken by historic figures to stop the genocide in Baku, Ganja and other regions. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The event was continued with discussion.&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/Sedr/1111111.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/Sedr/333333.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/Sedr/44444444.JPG\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 500px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
(5906, 'news', 320, 'en', 'short', '“Food Products&#39; Procurement and Supply” OJSC held a commemorative event dedicated to the 100-th anniversary of the March 31, Genocide of Azerbaijanis. '),
