(5950, 'news', 323, 'en', 'full', '<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">A group of employees of the Joint Stock Company participated in a seminar titled &quot;Risk Assessment in the Agricultural Sector&quot; organized by the World Bank.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">At the seminar was held in Baku office were discussed joint researches dedicated to the strengthening of the agricultural advisory services system designed by Dr.Carl Larsen World Bank Consultant. The research focusing on the strengthening of agricultural advisory services covers the economic significance of information and consulting services in the agrarian sector and the expansion of existing practices in this area. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Deputy Chief of International Economic Relations Nijat Rahimli, employee of the department Vasif Bayramov, employees of the Department of Information and Electronic Services Ayaz Karimov, Kamran Valiyev, as well as employees of Monitoring Department Elmir Guliyev and Rahim Ibrahimli made their suggestions on the discussion.&nbsp; </span></span></p>'),
