(5965, 'news', 324, 'en', 'full', '<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The Center for Economic Reform Analysis and Communications has announced its export summary for March. According to the summary covering January-February, &quot;Food Products&rsquo; Procurement and Supply&quot; OJSC has exported $ 1 million in volume. In the rating chart of state-owned export companies, the Joint Stock Company ranks sixth.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/upload/Sedr/95-45.jpg\" style=\"width: 750px; height: 492px;\" /></span></span></p>'),
